{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbcf30fa4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s5046"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5046"},"text":"§ 5046.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Labor standards for federally assisted projects, buildings, and works","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"All laborers and mechanics employed by contractors or subcontractors in the construction, alteration or repair, including painting and decorating of projects, buildings and works which are federally assisted under this chapter shall be paid wages at rates not less than those prevailing on similar construction in the locality as determined by the Secretary of Labor in accordance with sections 3141–3144, 3146, and 3147 of title 40. The Secretary of Labor shall have, with respect to such labor standards, the authority and functions set forth in Reorganization Plan Number 14 of 1950 (15 F.R. 3176; ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1267"},"text":"64 Stat. 1267","children":[],"tail":") and in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s3145"},"text":"section 3145 of title 40","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbcf30fa5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/113/tIV/s406"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–113, title IV, § 406","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/410"},"text":"87 Stat. 410","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbcf30fa6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbcf30fa7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbcf30fa8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/113"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–113","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/394"},"text":"87 Stat. 394","children":[],"tail":", known as the Domestic Volunteer Service Act of 1973, which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s4950"},"text":"section 4950 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Reorganization Plan Numbered 14 of 1950, referred to in text, is set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idbcf30fa9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In text, “sections 3141–3144, 3146, and 3147 of title 40” substituted for “the Davis-Bacon Act, as amended (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s276a"},"text":"40 U.S.C. 276a","children":[],"tail":"—276a–5)” and “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s3145"},"text":"section 3145 of title 40","children":[],"tail":"” substituted for “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-13/s2"},"text":"section 2 of the Act of June 13, 1934","children":[],"tail":", as amended ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/948"},"text":"48 Stat. 948","children":[],"tail":", ch. 492, as amended; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s276c"},"text":"40 U.S.C. 276c","children":[],"tail":")”, on authority of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217/s5/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217, § 5(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1303"},"text":"116 Stat. 1303","children":[],"tail":", the first section of which enacted Title 40, Public Buildings, Property, and Works."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
